  "text": "The CODEOWNERS infrastructure in grafana/grafana comprises several interconnected components:\n\n1. **GitHub Ownership Definition**: The `.github/CODEOWNERS` file contains pattern-based ownership rules mapping file paths to GitHub teams and users.\n\n2. **CI Validation**: The `.github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml` workflow runs on pull requests to the main branch, validating CODEOWNERS syntax, checking for duplicate patterns, detecting unowned files, and ensuring only teams are listed as owners when configured.\n\n3. **Manifest Generation Pipeline**: JavaScript scripts in `scripts/codeowners-manifest/` parse and index the CODEOWNERS file:\n   - `index.js` orchestrates the complete generation process with intelligent caching based on file hashes\n   - `metadata.js` generates SHA-256 hashes of both the CODEOWNERS file and repository files for cache validation\n   - `raw.js` invokes the `github-codeowners` CLI to produce raw audit data in JSONL format\n   - `generate.js` processes the raw audit data into three JSON manifest files: teams.json (list of codeowners), teams-by-filename.json (files mapped to owners), and filenames-by-team.json (owners mapped to files)\n   - `constants.js` defines all output paths for the manifest generation\n\n4. **Feature Management Integration**: Go code in `pkg/services/featuremgmt/` integrates codeowners with feature flags:\n   - `codeowners.go` defines the `codeowner` string type and constants for 29+ teams (e.g., `grafanaAppPlatformSquad`, `grafanaDashboardsSquad`, `grafanaDatavizSquad`)\n   - `models.go` includes the `codeowner` type in the `FeatureFlag` struct to track which team owns each feature\n   - `feature_toggle_api/types.go` exposes the codeowner field in the API's FeatureSpec as a JSON field\n   - `registry.go` references codeowner constants when registering feature flags\n\n5. **Test Coverage Integration**: The testing infrastructure uses CODEOWNERS for coverage tracking:\n   - `jest.config.codeowner.js` is a custom Jest configuration that filters tests and source files by team using the generated manifest\n   - `scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js` runs tests specifically for a given codeowner by loading the filenames-by-team.json manifest\n\n6. **npm Script Orchestration**: The `package.json` defines npm scripts that chain these components:\n   - `codeowners-manifest` invokes index.js for complete generation\n   - `codeowners-manifest:clean`, `:generate`, `:metadata`, `:raw` invoke individual scripts\n   - `test:coverage:by-codeowner` combines manifest generation with team-filtered test coverage reports\n\nThe infrastructure creates a bidirectional mapping between GitHub's CODEOWNERS file and feature management metadata, enabling team-based test coverage reporting and feature ownership tracking throughout the development workflow."
}

